-= Kitchen =-
You are in a kitchen. A standard kind of place. You begin to take stock of what's in the room.

You make out an open conventional looking fridge in the room. The fridge contains a fried red onion, a red hot pepper and a white onion. You can see a closed oven right there by you. You can see a table. On the table you can see a knife. I mean, just wow! Isn't TextWorld just the best? You make out a counter. On the counter you see a fried banana, a fried purple potato, a raw red potato and a cookbook. There's something strange about this thing being here, but you don't have time to worry about that now. Oh wow! Is that what I think it is? It is! It's a stove. The stove is conventional. But the thing is empty, unfortunately.

There is an open plain door leading east. You don't like doors? Why not try going north, that entranceway is not blocked by one.
